# Business Terminology Glossary (Example)

> Voice recordings often contain proper nouns (product names, technical jargon, people's names)
> that ASR systems mistranscribe. This file lists those terms so the LLM can correct them when
> generating notes.
>
> **How it's used**: The contents of this file are injected into the prompt under
> `[Business Terminology Glossary]`. The LLM checks the transcript against these patterns and
> restores the canonical form (e.g., "阿贾" → "Agile", "克劳德口德" → "Claude Code").
>
> **How to enable**:
> Set `glossary_path` in your `config.yaml`. Pointing it at this example works for
> general tech terms; you'll usually want to copy this and add your own team's project names
> and people's names.
>
> **Format**: One entry per line:
> - `Canonical form (often mistranscribed as "X", "Y", "Z")`
> - or simply `Canonical form` when there's no specific misrecognition pattern but you want
>   the LLM to favor this spelling/casing.
>
> Below is a starter set of commonly mistranscribed AI/dev terms. Add/remove freely.

## AI / Dev Tools

- Claude Code (often mistranscribed as "克劳德口德", "clod code", "Cloud Code")
- Cursor (often "靠瑟", "科瑟", "Coster")
- Codex (often "扣德克斯")
- Copilot (often "扣派洛")
- MCP / Model Context Protocol (often "MC P", "MCB")
- Sub-agent / 子 agent (often "撒不爱真")
- Skill / 技能包
- Hook / 钩子
- Prompt / 提示词
- RAG (often "rag", "瑞")
- Token (often "tokn")
- Embedding (often "因别丁")
- Fine-tuning / 微调
- Inference / 推理
- Figma (often "飞", "飞干嘛", "Mac 形式" — when context is design/prototype/UI)
- AST / 抽象语法树 (often "ST", "S T")
- Harness (often "哈尼斯" — in AI Agent framework context)
- Wiki (often "V", "位")
- Knowledge Graph / 知识图谱
- IDE
- Mock / Mock 文件 (often "Mac", "Mac 形式")

## General Engineering

- Agile -> 敏捷 (often "阿贾", "阿就")
- Method -> 方法 (often "买色", "麦色")
- Sprint -> 迭代 (often "斯普林特")
- Standup / 站会
- Retro / 复盘 (Retrospective)
- Code Review / 代码评审
- Pull Request / PR (often "P R")
- Merge / 合并
- Rebase
- Branch / 分支
- Commit
- CI/CD (often "C I C D")
- Pipeline
- Jenkins (often "詹金斯", "詹金森")
- Docker
- Kubernetes / k8s
- Repo / Repository
- Confluence (often "卡夫伦斯")
- Jira (often "几啦", "吉拉")
- Obsidian (often "奥比士", "奥比Sin")

## Project-Specific (add your own)

> Add your team's internal project/product/tool names here. ASR loves to mistranscribe these.

- (e.g.) Lobster -> OpenClaw  (when team verbally calls it "龙虾")

## People (add as encountered)

> Add coworkers' names so ASR doesn't mishear them. Easy way to maintain: every time
> the LLM produces a note, copy any newly-correct names back here.

- (Add as needed)
